---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const posts = (await getCollection('writing')).sort(
  (a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf()
);
const fmt = (d: Date) =>
  d.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', year: 'numeric' });
---
<Base>

<h1>Natwar</h1>

<p>I build data products. The current one is
<a href="https://conferencegrid.com">ConferenceGrid</a>, a conference database
for B2B teams. It reads six thousand conference sites and links the speakers,
sponsors, and exhibitors into one graph, so you can look up a company and see
every event it touches.</p>

<p>If you want to build something together,
<a href="mailto:natwar86@gmail.com">email me</a>.</p>

<h2>Projects</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://conferencegrid.com">ConferenceGrid</a>. Type a company,
  see every conference it sponsors, speaks at, or exhibits at. 6,000+
  conferences, 84,000 speakers, one graph.</li>
  <li><a href="https://subprocessors.xyz">Subprocessors</a>. A directory of who
  processes your data: 13,000 vendor relationships scraped from public
  subprocessor lists. The site is paused while I rethink the architecture, but
  the data exists. <a href="mailto:natwar86@gmail.com">Email me</a> if you want
  it.</li>
  <li><a href="https://developereducators.com">DeveloperEducators</a>. A
  directory of 5,000+ YouTube channels that teach programming, with engagement
  metrics, updated daily.</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/natwar86/foropensource">foropensource</a>.
  A community-maintained list of free products, services, and money for open
  source. 163 companies, each one verified.</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/natwar86/signal-listener">Signal Listener</a>.
  Watches reviews, Reddit, and other public feeds for sales signals. Built for
  Saltbox.</li>
  <li>Podcasts. A new project, in the works. More here soon.</li>
</ul>

{posts.length > 0 && (
  <>
    <h2>Writing</h2>
    <ul>
      {posts.map((post) => (
        <li>
          <a href={`/writing/${post.id}/`}>{post.data.title}</a><br />
          <span class="date">{fmt(post.data.date)}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </>
)}

<footer>
  <p>
    <a href="https://github.com/natwar86">github</a> ·
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/natwar/">linkedin</a> ·
    <a href="https://x.com/natwar86">x</a> ·
    <a href="mailto:natwar86@gmail.com">email</a>
  </p>
</footer>

</Base>
